            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Raymond Tan\u2019s story is woven into the very fabric of San Francisco. Born in the city\u2019s Sunset District, he was the only son of Chinese immigrants who poured their life savings into a small neighborhood grocery store. Raymond\u2019s childhood was a blend of American schooling and filial duty, his afternoons spent stocking shelves and his evenings translating utility bills for his parents. He was pragmatic and hardworking, enrolling at San Francisco State to study Business Administration with the goal of expanding the family enterprise.\n\nHis life took a sharp turn during his sophomore year when his father suffered a major heart attack. Without hesitation, Raymond left college to run the store full-time, trading his textbooks for an inventory ledger. For over a decade, he was the constant behind the counter, a familiar face in the neighborhood. Though he never earned his degree, he received a masterclass in logistics, customer service, and community.\n\nAfter his parents retired and sold the store, Raymond leveraged his practical expertise in the corporate retail world. He started on the sales floor of a downtown department store, quickly distinguishing himself with an intuitive grasp of merchandising and an old-school work ethic. Over two decades, he steadily climbed the ladder, his lack of a degree offset by his proven results. Now, as the manager of a gleaming flagship tech store near Union Square, he oversees a multi-million-dollar operation, a world away from the humble family grocery.\n\nRaymond\u2019s personal life is his anchor. He met his wife, Mei, a pediatric nurse, when she was a regular at his parents' store. Their 25-year marriage is a partnership built on shared values and quiet understanding. Their proudest achievement is their daughter, Chloe, now a sophomore at UC Davis\u2014living the university life he sacrificed.\n\nHis daily routine is a city rhythm: an early morning walk through Golden Gate Park, then the N Judah train downtown into the bustling heart of commerce. He navigates the demands of his high-pressure job with a placid demeanor, returning each evening to the peaceful familiarity of his Inner Richmond home. Raymond\u2019s dream isn\u2019t to climb higher on the corporate ladder, but to see Chloe graduate, debt-free. His aspiration is simpler: to one day travel through Italy with Mei, finally trading inventory reports for train tickets."
